#X text 815 15 ----------------------------------------------------------- \; ------ FUNCTIONALITY -------------------------------------- \; ----------------------------------------------------------- \; - AT INLET \, IT RECIEVES MIDI NOTE \, VELOCITY[0:1] AND OFF-DELAY TIME \; - A POLY OBJECT OF 16 CHANNEL OUTPUT MIDI NOTE AND VELOCITY \, PACKED WITH A SELECTOR AS THE FIRST ELEMENT AND OFF-DELAY TIME AS LAST ELEMENT \; - POLY OUTPUT OF VELOCITY 0 \, RECEIVED FROM "r \$0-FREE" WILL NOT PASS THROUGH TO ROUTE OBJECT AND THEIR ONLY PURPOSE IS TO FREE THE POLY OBJECT CHANNEL \; - AT ROUTE OBJECT SELECTOR WILL BE STRIPPED AND "MIDI NOTE \, VELOCITY \, OFF-DELAY" WILL BE ROUTED TO A WT.BANK SUBPATCHES \; - WHEN POLY GENERATES AN OUTPUT WITH A CHANNEL SELECTOR \, THAT CHANNEL WILL BE BUSY UNTIL \, POLY RECEVES ANOTHER INPUT OF THE SAME MIDI NOTE AND VELOCITY 0 THIS MESSAGE WILL BE SENT TO POLY FROM "WT.BANK"s RIGHT OUTLETS AFTER "OFF-DELAY + ADSR RELEASE TIME" \; - POLY IS SET TO "STEAL A CHANNEL" IN CASE NEW MIDI NOTE + VELOCITY(>0) COMES AND THERE IS NO FREE CHANNEL \; ----------------------------------------------------------- \; ------ FUTURE IMPROVEMENTS -------------------------------- \; ----------------------------------------------------------- \; - USE A CLONE OBJECT IF IT MAKES SENSE. A CLONE SHOULD BE INLETTED \$0 OF PARENT PATCH ("THIS PATCH") SO THAT IT CAN FIND THE \$0-WAVETABLE AND \$0-WAVE-ENVELOPE \; - WRITE ANOTHER EXTERNAL THAT COMBINES EVERYTHING UP TO THE WT.BANK \, THAT INSTEAD OF CIRCULATING BETWEEN 1->16 FIND THE FIRST FREE CHANNEL ---> NO ADVANTAGE --> NO SENSE AND PROBABLY WORSE PERFORMANCE! \; - MULTIPLE CURSOR DIFFERENT COLORS PER CHANNEL \; - MAYBE NEED TO ADD MORE CHANNEL LATER ON \; - DIFFERENT ADSR VALUES RECIEVED FROM THE SEQUENCER?? - MAYBE.. \; ----------------------------------------------------------- \; ------ NOTES ---------------------------------------------- \; ----------------------------------------------------------- \; - WAVE LOADED SHOULD ALREADY BE NORMALIZED \; - VELOCITY(AMPLITUDE) LEVEL [0:1]. FURTHER AMPLIFICATIONS OUTSIDE OUTLET~ \; - SHAPE OF ADSR ENVELOPE IS DEFINES INTERNALY AND SAVED. COULD LATER MAKE A DESIGN TO RECEIE THIS FROM A SEQEUNCER AS WELL IF NEEDED \;, f 61;
